The '''Canada U-17 women's national soccer team''' is a youth [[association football|soccer]] team operated under the [[Canadian Soccer Association]].  Its primary role is the development of players in preparation for the full [[Canada women's national soccer team|Women's National Team]].  The team's most recent major tournament was the [[2010 CONCACAF Women's U-17 Championship]], in which the Canadian team finished as first-time champions. The team competes in a variety of competitions, including the biennial [[FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup]], which is the top competition for this age group.

==History==
At the [[2010 FIFA U-17 Women's World Cup]] the team was eliminated after the preliminry round.

